[2] Africa: endemic diseases
Date: Thu 26 May 2022
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/more-than-ebola-drc-reports-cholera-measles-monkeypox-plague-and-typhoid-outbreaks-44511/


More than Ebola: DRC reports cholera, measles, monkeypox, plague, and typhoid outbreaks
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The ongoing Ebola virus disease (EVD) outbreak in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) has spread out to a new Health Zone with a new confirmed case reported on [19 May 2022] in Mama Balako Health Area, Wangata Health Zone in Mbandaka City, Equateur Province.

Two Health Zones (Mbandaka and Wangata) and 3 Health areas are now affected (Libiki, Motema Pembe for Mbandaka Health Zone and Mama Balako for Wangata health Zone).

As of [22 May 2022], a total of 5 cases including 4 confirmed cases and 1 probable case with 5 deaths (case fatality ratio (CFR): 100%) are reported.

However, it's not just Ebola the country is battling:

Cholera
In 2022 through 1 May, 5485 suspected cholera cases including 79 deaths (CFR: 1.4%) were recorded in 54 health zones across 11 provinces of the Democratic Republic of the Congo.

Measles
From [1 Jan-1 May 2022], 47 514 suspected measles cases and 684 deaths (CFR 1.4%) were reported in 349 health zones in 26 provinces.

Monkeypox
In the 1st 4 months of 2022, DRC has reported 1238 monkeypox cases, including 57 deaths (CFR 4.6%).

Plague
Through [1 May 2022], DRC has seen 88 cases of plague, including 2 deaths (2.0% CFR). Lokpa remains the epicentre reporting 95% of cases reported this year.

Typhoid fever
In 2022, through 1 May, 634 401 suspected cases of typhoid fever including 279 deaths were recorded in the Democratic Republic of the Congo.

In addition, outbreaks of yellow fever, meningitis and circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) are reported and being monitored.

