[The incidence of many endemic diseases has been exacerbated by COVID, civil war, and political instability in DR Congo. It is a challenging situation and healthcare is suffering. But the country has handled the most recent Ebola outbreaks so successfully, that one would hope this knowledge could be transferred to other infectious disease problems. See Venkatesan P. Managing infectious diseases in DR Congo: lessons learned from Ebola. Lancet Microbe. 2020; 1(4): e153; https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lanmic/article/PIIS2666-5247(20)30102-6/fulltext. - Mod.LK

